        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix/redact app password overmasking 94254",
        "body": "Fixes #94254.\n\n## Summary\n\n`redactSensitiveFieldValue()` in `src/logging/redact.ts` has a too-broad `STRUCTURED_APP_PASSWORD_FIELD_RE` that includes generic field names (`text`, `content`, `message`, `error`, etc.), causing ordinary kebab-case identifiers to be falsely masked as Apple app-specific passwords.\n\n## Changes\n\n1. **Narrowed field regex** — `STRUCTURED_APP_PASSWORD_FIELD_RE` now only matches Apple-specific fields (`apple`, `icloud`, `appSpecificPassword`, etc.)\n2. **Three-tier redaction logic:**\n   - Tier 1 (Apple fields) — mask ALL 4x4 tokens fail-closed\n   - Tier 2 (secret-context) — wordlist precision\n   - Tier 3 (generic fields) — only scan with Apple context; fail-closed if context present, skip if absent\n3. **Expanded wordlist** — `BENIGN_APP_PASSWORD_WORDS` from 10→220+ common 4-letter words\n4. **Credential context gate** — `hasApplePasswordContext()` detects Apple/iCloud keywords\n\n## Current-head real behavior proof\n\n```\nTier 1 — Apple fields: mask ALL 4x4 tokens (fail-closed)\n  ✅ apple field masks random token\n  ✅ appSpecificPassword masks dict token (fail-closed)\n\nTier 2 — Secret-context: wordlist precision\n  ✅ JWT masked in secret-context\n  ✅ dict kebab preserved in secret-context\n\nTier 3a — WITH Apple context: mask all 4x4 tokens\n  ✅ iCloud context → token masked\n  ✅ 'app password' context → token masked\n  ✅ 'apple id' context → token masked\n\nTier 3b — NO Apple context: skip scan, preserve everything\n  ✅ non-dict token preserved (no context)\n  ✅ random token preserved (no context)\n  ✅ dict kebab preserved (no context)\n```\n\n## Unit tests\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/logging/redact.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  115 passed (115)\n```\n\n## Review\n\n- Manually verified\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
